  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Creating GIS Data in Python from Scratch\n",
    "\n",
    "This chapter focuses on creating and manipulating GIS data entirely in Python, with an emphasis on **Shapely**, the core library for geometric operations.  \n",
    "By the end of this chapter, you'll be able to create, transform, analyze, and export geometry data using **Shapely** and **GeoPandas**."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "## 1. Introduction to Shapely\n",
    "\n",
    "[Shapely](https://shapely.readthedocs.io/) is a Python library for **creating and manipulating planar geometric objects**.  \n",
    "It is the foundation for spatial data operations in Python and integrates seamlessly with **GeoPandas**.\n",
    "\n",
    "Shapely allows you to create and analyze geometries like:\n",
    "- Points (for locations)\n",
    "- LineStrings (for linear features like roads or rivers)\n",
    "- Polygons (for areas like lakes, parks, or buildings)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "## 2. Creating Geometries\n",
    "\n",
    "### Importing Shapely Geometry Classes"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from shapely.geometry import Point, LineString, Polygon"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Creating a Point"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "p = Point(77.5946, 12.9716)  # Bengaluru\n",
    "print(p.x, p.y)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "You can also create **3D points**:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "p3d = Point(77.5946, 12.9716, 920)\n",
    "print(p3d.z)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Creating a LineString"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "line = LineString([(77.5, 12.9), (77.6, 13.0), (77.7, 13.2)])\n",
    "print(line.length)\n",
    "print(line.coords[:])"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Creating a Polygon"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "poly = Polygon([(77.5, 12.9), (77.7, 13.1), (77.9, 13.0), (77.5, 12.9)])\n",
    "print(poly.area)\n",
    "print(poly.bounds)  # (minx, miny, maxx, maxy)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "## 3. Common Shapely Attributes and Methods\n",
    "\n",
    "### Point Methods\n",
    "| Method | Description |\n",
    "|---------|--------------|\n",
    "| `.x`, `.y`, `.z` | Access coordinate values |\n",
    "| `.buffer(distance)` | Creates a circular buffer polygon around the point |\n",
    "| `.distance(other)` | Calculates Euclidean distance to another geometry |\n",
    "| `.within(other)` | Checks if point lies within another geometry |\n",
    "| `.intersects(other)` | Checks if it touches or overlaps another geometry |\n",
    "\n",
    "### Example: Point Buffer"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "p = Point(0, 0)\n",
    "buffered = p.buffer(10)\n",
    "print(buffered.area)  # Area of circle with radius 10"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### LineString Methods\n",
    "| Method | Description |\n",
    "|---------|--------------|\n",
    "| `.length` | Total length of line |\n",
    "| `.coords` | Returns list of coordinates |\n",
    "| `.interpolate(distance)` | Returns a point at given distance along line |\n",
    "| `.simplify(tolerance)` | Simplifies line by reducing vertices |"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "line = LineString([(0, 0), (1, 1), (2, 2)])\n",
    "print(line.interpolate(1))  # Point at distance 1 along line"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Polygon Methods\n",
    "| Method | Description |\n",
    "|---------|--------------|\n",
    "| `.area` | Polygon area |\n",
    "| `.centroid` | Returns the geometric center |\n",
    "| `.bounds` | Bounding box (minx, miny, maxx, maxy) |\n",
    "| `.exterior` | Outer boundary as LineString |\n",
    "| `.interiors` | List of holes within polygon |\n",
    "| `.contains(other)` | True if polygon fully contains another geometry |\n",
    "| `.touches(other)` | True if boundaries touch |\n",
    "| `.difference(other)` | Returns area difference |\n",
    "| `.union(other)` | Merges two polygons |"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "## 4. Geometry Relationships and Boolean Operations\n",
    "\n",
    "Shapely supports powerful geometric predicates and operations.\n",
    "\n",
    "### Boolean Operations\n",
    "| Operation | Example | Description |\n",
    "|------------|----------|--------------|\n",
    "| `intersects` | `poly1.intersects(poly2)` | Checks if they touch/overlap |\n",
    "| `contains` | `poly1.contains(p)` | True if poly1 fully contains p |\n",
    "| `within` | `p.within(poly1)` | True if p inside poly1 |\n",
    "| `equals` | `geom1.equals(geom2)` | Checks geometric equality |\n",
    "\n",
    "### Set-like Operations\n",
    "| Operation | Example | Description |\n",
    "|------------|----------|--------------|\n",
    "| `union` | `poly1.union(poly2)` | Combines both areas |\n",
    "| `intersection` | `poly1.intersection(poly2)` | Common overlapping region |\n",
    "| `difference` | `poly1.difference(poly2)` | Removes overlapping part |\n",
    "| `symmetric_difference` | `poly1.symmetric_difference(poly2)` | Keeps non-overlapping parts |\n",
    "\n",
    "Example:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from shapely.geometry import Polygon\n",
    "\n",
    "poly1 = Polygon([(0,0), (2,0), (2,2), (0,2)])\n",
    "poly2 = Polygon([(1,1), (3,1), (3,3), (1,3)])\n",
    "\n",
    "intersection = poly1.intersection(poly2)\n",
    "union = poly1.union(poly2)\n",
    "difference = poly1.difference(poly2)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "## 5. Geometric Manipulation\n",
    "\n",
    "### Buffering"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "p = Point(0, 0)\n",
    "circle = p.buffer(5)\n",
    "circle.boundary.length  # Circumference"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Simplification"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "poly = Polygon([(0,0), (1,0.1), (2,0.2), (3,0), (3,1), (0,1)])\n",
    "simple_poly = poly.simplify(0.2)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Convex Hull\n",
    "Creates the smallest convex polygon that encloses all points."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from shapely.geometry import MultiPoint\n",
    "\n",
    "points = MultiPoint([(0,0), (1,2), (2,1), (2,2)])\n",
    "hull = points.convex_hull"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Centroid"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "poly = Polygon([(0,0), (4,0), (4,4), (0,4)])\n",
    "print(poly.centroid)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Bounds and Envelope"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "print(poly.bounds)     # (minx, miny, maxx, maxy)\n",
    "print(poly.envelope)   # Minimum bounding rectangle"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "## 6. Combining Shapely with GeoPandas\n",
    "\n",
    "After creating geometries, we can integrate them into **GeoDataFrames** for storage and export."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import geopandas as gpd\n",
    "from shapely.geometry import Point, Polygon\n",
    "\n",
    "cities = ['Delhi', 'Mumbai', 'Chennai']\n",
    "geometry = [Point(77.1, 28.7), Point(72.8, 19.0), Point(80.2, 13.0)]\n",
    "\n",
    "gdf = gpd.GeoDataFrame({'city': cities}, geometry=geometry, crs='EPSG:4326')\n",
    "gdf.plot(markersize=80, color='crimson')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Export Formats"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "gdf.to_file('cities.geojson', driver='GeoJSON')\n",
    "gdf.to_file('cities.gpkg', layer='cities', driver='GPKG')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "## 7. Practical GIS Examples Using Shapely\n",
    "\n",
    "### 7.1 Creating Buffer Zones Around Locations"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "schools = [Point(77.5, 12.9), Point(77.6, 13.0)]\n",
    "buffers = [s.buffer(0.05) for s in schools]"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 7.2 Checking Spatial Relationships"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "city_boundary = Polygon([(77.4,12.8),(77.8,12.8),(77.8,13.2),(77.4,13.2)])\n",
    "school = Point(77.6, 12.9)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(school.within(city_boundary))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 7.3 Clipping a Line by a Polygon"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "line = LineString([(77.3, 12.9), (77.9, 13.1)])\n",
    "clipped = line.intersection(city_boundary)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 7.4 Calculating Area and Length"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "print(city_boundary.area)\n",
    "print(line.length)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "## 8. Summary of Common Shapely Functions\n",
    "\n",
    "| Category | Function | Description |\n",
    "|-----------|-----------|-------------|\n",
    "| **Creation** | `Point`, `LineString`, `Polygon`, `MultiPoint`, `MultiPolygon` | Create geometries |\n",
    "| **Analysis** | `area`, `length`, `centroid`, `bounds`, `envelope` | Measure properties |\n",
    "| **Relationships** | `contains`, `within`, `intersects`, `touches`, `equals` | Spatial relationships |\n",
    "| **Operations** | `union`, `difference`, `intersection`, `buffer`, `simplify` | Modify shapes |\n",
    "| **Transformation** | `translate`, `rotate`, `scale` | Move or reshape geometries |"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "## 9. Real-World Use Cases\n",
    "\n",
    "- **Urban Planning:** Create 500m buffers around schools to check overlapping noise zones.  \n",
    "- **Environmental Studies:** Calculate intersection area of flood zones and forest cover.  \n",
    "- **Transportation:** Simplify road networks for visualization and performance.  \n",
    "- **Boundary Management:** Merge administrative polygons to create regional boundaries."
   ]
  },
  {
